Text.Value: I'm merely pointing out this whole strategy is sorely lacking...
Another word and it won't be the goblins you have to worry about!
That's to say me at the front while the others stay back and do as I say?
Battle formation. Now.
Oh, share your tactical wisdom with us then!
Look at this place. Like a pen of hogs waiting for the butcher's knife. We need to act!
There you go, Rolan - the glory of dying first is all yours. Happy?
Oh, perish the thought they overhear a little honesty once in their short lives -
Trust me, I'm feeling both anger and despair.
Exceedingly happy. But I won't be dying.
Please! I can hardly hear myself think over the pair of you.
Rolan in back, where he has time to cast. You two are his shield.
Enough! Both of you!
Shut it just for once, you insufferable, oafish -
Fine, fine. Agreed.
... Rolan...?
Rolan front and centre - you two don't want to get caught in his crossfire.
Stop it! Listen to someone else for once.

EditorData.NodeContext: Exasperated - gesturing to the player to continue.

Text.Value: Why, I think I'm almost in agreement with you on that score.
Quiet! Some of the children might hear you.
I can live with that... I hope. What about you two?
Or shot through with goblin arrows.
Fine. As long as I don't have to listen to any complaints in the meantime.
Agreed.
Let's just stick to the plan, now that we have one. Agreed?
You three are making me root for the goblins.
Leave.
Let them argue. Right now, anger's more useful than despair.
That's as close to an agreement as we're likely to get. Let's keep it that way.
No, don't - please.
We could've been far away from this place by now.
So be it. I'll take a mediocre plan over nothing.

Synopsis: Rolan (the prodigy) bickers with his Cal and Lia. The player can choose to weigh in or not. Soldiers, rangers or fighters can give some specific advice on their battle formation.
